HEADWORD: Petrocoptis
<hw>Petrocoptis</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of perennial
tussock-forming rock plants; native to the Pyrenees and mountains of
Northern Spain; it is similar to and sometimes placed in the genus
<gen>Lychnis</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Petrocoptis</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
